org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.qptl

Class QPTLBinary

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.Logic
      • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.qptl.QPTL
        • org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.qptl.QPTLBinary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, NegationNormalForm<QPTL>, PrenexNormalForm<QPTL>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    QPTLAnd, QPTLBackto, QPTLEquivalence, QPTLImplication, QPTLOr, QPTLRelease, QPTLSince, QPTLTrigger, QPTLUnless, QPTLUntil

    public abstract class QPTLBinary
extends QPTL
    This class represents QPTL formulae formed by a binary operator, for example "f U g", "f R g", "f S g", "f B g", "f T g", "f --> g", or "f <--> g".
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
